The paper discusses the security vulnerabilities of the LTE protocol and the potential for location tracking, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the implementation of rogue base stations and exploits, which could fall under the category of system security (cs.SY). The use of LTE networks for Machine to Machine (M2M) communication systems and the Internet of Things (IoT) could also place this paper under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes mitigations for the security threats discussed, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
